column7: How much $$$ can you make as a ghostwriter?
column9:
I started ghostwriting in 2016.

Since then I’ve ghostwritten for 300+ different industry leaders:

* CEOs
* Silicon Valley Founders
* Grammy-winning musicians

And more.

And every day, I get tons of messages about how to get into
ghostwriting, how to scale as a ghostwriter, and what skills you
need to master to become a highly-profitable ghostwriter.

So, to help you kickstart you ghostwriting business, here are the
8 most common questions I get asked all in one place.

Let’s dive in!

Prefer to watch a video version of this newsletter?

​Click here to watch this over on YouTube. (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/75uo4eeqwos8hkgvrzqtzhw34m666cn/z2h2nr6ec7u3q26xnzaz/aHR0cHM6Ly95b3V0dS5iZS9rYzZQWmVBdElhRT9zaT1lV2E2SGFsMk44eFc2V3Vk
)​

(
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/75uo4eeqwos8hkgvrzqtzhw34m666cn/p8hzn3o6squznw6omefr/aHR0cHM6Ly95b3V0dS5iZS9rYzZQWmVBdElhRT9zaT1lV2E2SGFsMk44eFc2V3Vk
)​

*****************************************************************
Question 1: Should you target a specific industry or play the
field and pick a niche later?
*****************************************************************

When starting out, it’s important to pick a niche where you have
an Information Advantage.

Your Information Advantage is where:

* You already speak the industry lingo
* You know the pain points of your target client
* You know what outcomes these kinds of people want

When I first started, I attracted founders and executives from
every kind of industry.

But I didn’t have an Information Advantage in every single
industry on planet Earth! But if you do have domain expertise,
you should write for that particular industry because your
Information Advantage means you can charge more.

Nicolas Cole 🚢-->

@Nicolascole77

Ghostwriters:

Niche down until you have an information advantage. Clients
aren’t paying you to "write words". They’re paying you to write
the right words in a way that is fluent within their industry.

If you can't, talented writer or not, you have no value in that
industry. (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/75uo4eeqwos8hkgvrzqtzhw34m666cn/3ohphdu7e5mg0wip/aHR0cHM6Ly94LmNvbS9OaWNvbGFzY29sZTc3L3N0YXR1cy8xNzk3Njk3NDc1NzE0NzI0MjQz
)

https://click.convertkit-mail.com/75uo4eeqwos8hkgvrzqtzhw34m666cn/3ohphdu7e5mg0wip/aHR0cHM6Ly94LmNvbS9OaWNvbGFzY29sZTc3L3N0YXR1cy8xNzk3Njk3NDc1NzE0NzI0MjQz
)
​
So, look for the pattern of who’s the easiest to work with
(because of your Information Advantage) and which clients are the
most efficient for you.

*****************************************************************
Question 2: What’s the most challenging part of ghostwriting for
such high-profile clients?
*****************************************************************

The biggest challenge is TIME.

You are dealing with people who in many cases are managing
anywhere between 5-10 employees all the way up to thousands of
employees. You’re dealing with people who are used to being in
power dynamics where they’re the ones telling other people what
to do. Many also have families.

>From the moment they wake up to the moment they go to sleep, they
have people pinging and dinging them asking for things.

So, what is a busy CEO really looking for?
------------------------------------------

Someone to manage them.

The worst thing you could do as a service provider is start
working with someone like that and then say, “Let me know what
you need,” because that’s already their whole life.

What they value more than anything else is your ability to:

* Follow up eight times
* Not get frustrated when you don’t hear back
* Move the ball forward and take radical accountability

Yes, they value this even more than your writing ability.

*****************************************************************
Question 3: How do you get into the mind of a client to produce
meaningful work?
*****************************************************************

You don’t want to go onto your call with a CEO and ask, “What
ideas do you have?” because they aren’t going to know what to
say.

Remember, you’re the expert here—so guide them.

Winning ideas are the overlap between:

* What this person would be most equipped to talk about * This
could be broad for your client (e.g. CEOs can talk about morning
routines, hiring, firing, etc)
* Or very deep, domain-specific knowledge

* And what topics other people would find most interesting

Show up with ideas that would perform well and speak to their
target audience.

Nicolas Cole 🚢-->

@Nicolascole77

95% of my ghostwriting clients had the same "voice":

• To the point
• No harsh language
• No flowery language
• Minimal industry jargon
• Simple and easy to understand
• Formal tone without being verbose

Most of the time, they just wanted to sound confident. (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/75uo4eeqwos8hkgvrzqtzhw34m666cn/48hvh7ur4dl8l5uq/aHR0cHM6Ly94LmNvbS9OaWNvbGFzY29sZTc3L3N0YXR1cy8xODA5NjU2MjMwNjE4NTcxMTMy
)

)
​

*****************************************************************
Question 4: Should I start ghostwriting if I’m a new writer and
haven’t published anything online before?
*****************************************************************

Can you?

Yes.

Should you?

Sure.

But is your life easier or harder by not writing for yourself on
the internet?

Well, it’s harder. We have plenty of people in our Premium
Ghostwriting Academy (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/75uo4eeqwos8hkgvrzqtzhw34m666cn/reh8h9u0gldzd7s6/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucHJlbWl1bWdob3N0d3JpdGluZ2FjYWRlbXkuY29tLw==
) who don’t write on the internet and don’t write under their own
name. They don’t build a personal brand. They use cold outreach
and tap their network to land clients. So it can work if you’re
not already writing online.

But it’s worth asking how many more clients could you attract and
how much easier would it be to convert those clients if you used
yourself as practice?

Dickie Bush 🚢-->

@dickiebush

A quick & easy way to upskill as a ghostwriter:

Practice In Public.

• Ghostwrite eBooks? Write eBooks for yourself.
• Ghostwrite LI posts? Write LI posts for yourself.
• Ghostwrite IG captions? Write IG captions for yourself.

Prove it works for you, first. (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/75uo4eeqwos8hkgvrzqtzhw34m666cn/8ghqh3ulm6dndxbl/aHR0cHM6Ly94LmNvbS9kaWNraWVidXNoL3N0YXR1cy8xODE3OTkwNjcxNDgwODM2Mzc0
)

https://click.convertkit-mail.com/75uo4eeqwos8hkgvrzqtzhw34m666cn/8ghqh3ulm6dndxbl/aHR0cHM6Ly94LmNvbS9kaWNraWVidXNoL3N0YXR1cy8xODE3OTkwNjcxNDgwODM2Mzc0
)
​
Practice on yourself, write what you want to master under your
name, and then rent whatever’s working to other people.

********************************************************
Question 5: How do you measure success as a ghostwriter?
********************************************************

This question reveals how little people understand about their
value.

Often, freelance writers think their offer needs to promise
something specific:

* “I will get you 10,000 followers in 60 days”
* Or “I will make you an extra 30 grand from your sales funnel”

First, nobody in marketing has any idea whether something is
going to work or not.

Second, an example.

I built my ghostwriting agency doing nothing but 800-word
articles. We ended up writing more articles each month than Inc.
magazine or Forbes, doing over $2 million a year in revenue. Not
once did I promise specific follower counts or revenue increases.

The way we framed the value was simple:

* Do you understand it’s important to write on the internet?
​
* When you write on the internet, people view you as a thought
leader so it’s easier to connect with peers and inbound
opportunities are likely to increase
​
* Right now you’re not writing on the internet
​
* When we work together, you will be writing on the internet

The value is that zero-to-one moment. They don’t have those
things now but they will when you work with them.

That’s the value you sell.

**************************************************************
Question 6: What types of businesses should I steer away from?
**************************************************************

This goes back to where you have an Information Advantage.

When I was ghostwriting, I started to avoid clients where I
didn’t want to know anything about their industry. Some early
clients were in industries I knew nothing about but was excited
to learn more about (for example, crypto in 2016 and 2017).

So, the real question comes down to what you want to learn.

I had clients in other industries (like affiliate marketing and
grey hat marketing) that I wasn’t interested in. But I continued
saying yes to clients in industries I didn’t know much about but
found interesting.

Consider steering away from businesses where:

* It’s too time-consuming, even if interesting, because time is
your primary asset
​
* There are regulations on what you can/can’t say (medicine,
finance, health and wellness, etc.)

Pro tip: If you learn to navigate these regulations, it increases
your value tremendously to those companies.

***************************************************************
Question 7: How do I come up with different topics for clients?
***************************************************************

All content leads back to 5 content buckets:

* Mission. What is the founder’s/CEO’s mission? What are they
trying to do and why does it matter?
​
* Industry Trends. What’s currently happening? Can they comment
on new data and/or studies?
​
* Futurism. Where is this industry headed? Ask them to project
current trends 5-10 years out.
​
* Education. What could they explain to others in their role or
those aspiring to be in their role?
​
* Stories. What unique experiences can they share?

You can go back to these 5 content buckets over and over again
and they work for any leader in any industry.

*****************************************************
Question 8: Is there a ceiling for solo ghostwriters?
*****************************************************

Most people ask this question way earlier than necessary.

Getting to $10k/month as a ghostwriter is incredibly easy with
just a handful of skills. The difference between $10k and
$20k/month comes down to outreach effort and the ability to sell
on the phone.

This pattern continues up to $30k-$50k. Around $40k-$50k, you’ll
hit a ceiling as an individual. There are some outliers . For
example, New York Times bestselling authors who ghostwrite for
celebrities can make $1-2M yearly, but they only do 1-2 projects
per year.

For the average person, at around $30k/$40k/$50k per month, you
have two main options:

* Stay there and maybe launch digital products
​
* Scale into a small agency by hiring other writers, account
managers, and sales reps

Many people ask about scaling before they’ve even reached $10k
per month.

This is “Early 20s Syndrome”—constantly looking for the next
thing instead of focusing on what’s right in front of you.

Nicolas Cole 🚢-->

@Nicolascole77

years of mistakes.

https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn0v79gf6h8lo4v00bg/kkhmh2ulpz6v5mbk/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS90aGVqYXlhbHRvL3N0YXR1cy8xNDk4Mzc2MDE1NTkyMTc3NjgwP3M9MjE=
) (Twitter thread)
* ​How to grow on YouTube (without getting lucky) (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn0v79gf6h8lo4v00bg/58hvh8umw3k2nlu7/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9QYWRkeUc5Ni9zdGF0dXMvMTUwNDQ1MjIyNDczMDI0MzA3Ng==
) (Twitter thread)
* ​Mr. Beast's thumbnail designer's tips (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn0v79gf6h8lo4v00bg/25h2h9u2xl4w8lf8/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS90aGVKYXlBbHRvL3N0YXR1cy8xNTA0NTAwOTUyNDEzNDgzMDEy
) (Twitter thread)

These resources have genuinely changed my life, and I hope they
can change yours (for the better) too.

But, while reading is incredibly valuable, it’s important to
remember:

👉 Don’t let reading replace doing the thing.

👉 Avoid using books as a way to procrastinate from real-world
action.

👉 Focus on the sections of a book that actually apply to your
current goals.

(Here’s a helpful guide to smarter reading which I also think is
very good: 43 Reading Tips from Naval Ravikant (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/lmur20nw6mimhn0v79gf6h8lo4v00bg/qvh8h8ur3eop4zbg/aHR0cHM6Ly94LmNvbS9BbGV4QW5kQm9va3NfL3N0YXR1cy8xNzM0NTcxODE1NjkzOTMwODY3P214PTI=
).)

Your next step then is to pick one book, one strategy, or one
video and start applying it today.

Reading can spark ideas, but doing is what creates change.

Hope this is useful ❤️

Have a great week!

Ali xx

column7: What is the I School Advantage?
column9:
<https://ischoolonline.berkeley.edu/data-science/>
 
Dear Prospective Student,
 
The UC Berkeley School of Information (I School) educates professionals and scholars to understand the problems and possibilities of information, to develop models of information practice, and to design useful and usable information applications, services, and solutions.
 
Our graduates have gone on to work at well-known Bay Area companies that include Apple, Google, Facebook, Salesforce, Twitter, and LinkedIn, as well as at nonprofits like Kaiser Permanente and established businesses like Wells Fargo and Chevron. Many of our graduates take advantage of the opportunity to get in on the ground floor to create or work for start-ups.
 
We asked our students: "What is the I School advantage?"

"The 'I School advantage' is a combination of robust technology paired with an excellent curriculum taught by some of the best academicians in the field of data science and applied analytics. The technology not only allows for a strong online classroom setting but also supports group projects where I am typically collaborating with students across multiple continents. The Master of Information and Data Science (MIDS) curriculum is so applicable to my career, I have actually implemented solutions for clients within days of learning about them in class."
-Chris Bennett, Co-founder and COO at Intelisent 
Hartford, Connecticut
 
"I was drawn to the datascience@berkeley program because of its broad and rigorous curriculum, covering everything from the basics to advanced topics in research design, statistics, and machine learning. The immersive online classroom experience with live video interactions, the professionalism and dedication of the professors, the supportive staff, the online Slack channels, and plenty of group work all make it feel like a real classroom experience."
- Subhashini Raghunathan, Software Engineer at Versive 
Seattle, Washington
 
"Being online is a tremendous advantage for the MIDS program at the School of Information (I School). It provides access to students from around the world, bringing in a very high caliber of professionals from diverse backgrounds. This leads to many different perspectives and a rich learning environment. MIDS students have sought this program out and are extremely engaged and looking to learn from both the program and their peers."
- Michael Amodeo, Civil Engineer and GIS Analyst 
New York City, New York
 
The Master of Information and Data Science (MIDS) program's multidisciplinary curriculum and network of top professionals prepare you to be a leader in the ever-evolving field of data science. Take the next step to join the MIDS network and complete your application.
 
GO TO YOUR APPLICATION >>
<https://apply.datascience.berkeley.edu/signup>
 
The early action deadline for the January 2026 cohort is August 6. Applications received by the early action deadline may be eligible for an application fee waiver. To receive the waiver, reach out to your admissions counselor before you submit your application by the priority application deadline. If you do not receive the fee waiver confirmation email and pay an application fee, we will not be able to reimburse you.

If you have any questions about the MIDS program or the application process, please contact your Admissions Counselor directly at 855-678-6437 or slee2@datascience.berkeley.edu.
 
Sincerely,
 
datascience@berkeley Admissions
UC Berkeley School of Information
ischoolonline.berkeley.edu
<https://ischoolonline.berkeley.edu/data-science/>

 Confirmation of Sub Teacher Hiring Event Dear Candace Grant,

You are scheduled for 11:30 AM for the Substitute Teacher Hiring Event on
07/30/25. Please plan to arrive 15 minutes early. Candidates who arrive late may
be turned away. Please note that the entire event will take approximately 1 hour
to complete.

Location: 
**Please DO NOT share this information with anyone. This event is by invitation
ONLY and all other candidates will be turned away at the door.**
Forest Hills Tower- Queens UFT Building
118-35 Queens Boulevard, 8th Floor
Forest Hills, NY 11375
Time: 11:30 AM
Date: 07/30/25

What to Wear:
Dress professionally for your interview. You will be speaking with school and
office personnel. 

What to Bring:
*Valid Government-Issued Photo ID (e.g., driver’s license, US Passport,
Permanent Resident Card, etc.)
*Social Security Card

What to Expect:
(1) You will be asked to show your valid government-issued photo ID (e.g.,
driver’s license, US Passport, Permanent Resident Card, etc.) to security to
enter the building as well as at the welcome table when you check in. Please
make sure that the name on your identification is the name in which you
registered. Copies of identification will not be accepted.
(2) You will complete a brief interview. 

We look forward to seeing you on 07/30/25 at 11:30 AM.

NYC Public Schools
Division of Human Resources
